==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[drincan]]'', from Germanic ''*drinka-''.  Cognate with Dutch ''[[drinken#Dutch|drinken]]'', German ''[[trinken]]'', Swedish ''[[dricka]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|drĭngk}}, {{IPA|/drɪŋk/}}, {{SAMPA|/drINk/}}

===Verb===
{{irregverb|'''to drink'''|'''[[drinks]]'''|'''[[drank]]'''|'''[[drunk]]'''|'''[[drinking]]'''}}

# To [[consume]] a [[liquid]] through the [[mouth]].
#: ''You can lead a horse to water but you can't make him '''drink'''.''
# To [[consume]] [[alcoholic]] [[beverage]]s.
#: ''No thanks, I don't '''drink'''.''
# To consume [[soup]]
#: ''To '''drink''' or eat soup, depends on how thick it is''

